# =============================================================================
# MASTER .GITIGNORE — All Major Programming Languages & Environments
# =============================================================================
# Why use .gitignore?
#   Git tracks every file in your project unless told otherwise. Many tools
#   generate files that are machine-specific, auto-rebuilt, contain secrets,
#   or are simply too large/noisy for version control. Committing these causes
#   merge conflicts, bloated repos, security leaks, and broken cross-platform
#   builds. This file tells Git to silently ignore them.
# =============================================================================


# =============================================================================
# SECTION 1 — OPERATING SYSTEM FILES
# Generated automatically by macOS, Windows, and Linux. They encode local
# display preferences and file metadata that differ per machine — committing
# them causes noisy diffs and conflicts for every collaborator.
# =============================================================================

# --- macOS ---

# Finder folder-view settings (icon positions, sort order)
.DS_Store
# Variant created on network drives
.DS_Store?
# Resource fork / extended-attribute sidecar files
._*
# Spotlight search index for a volume
.Spotlight-V100
# macOS Trash metadata on external volumes
.Trashes
# AppleDouble-format resource forks
.AppleDouble
# Launch Services override database
.LSOverride
# Custom folder icon file (has a hidden carriage return in the name)
Icon
# Apple desktop database
.AppleDB
# Apple desktop metadata
.AppleDesktop

# --- Windows ---

# Explorer thumbnail cache — per-machine, not project data
Thumbs.db
# Encrypted variant of thumbnail cache
Thumbs.db:encryptable
# Windows Media Center thumbnail cache
ehthumbs.db
# Vista-era thumbnail cache
ehthumbs_vista.db
# Folder customisation settings (layout, icon, tooltip)
Desktop.ini
# Windows Recycle Bin metadata folder
$RECYCLE.BIN/
# Windows Cabinet compressed archive (build artifact)
*.cab
# Windows Installer package (build artifact)
*.msi
# Windows Installer merge module
*.msm
# Windows Installer patch
*.msp
# Windows shortcut — machine-specific absolute paths inside
*.lnk
# Case-insensitive match for Desktop.ini
[Dd]esktop.ini
# Cygwin crash dump
*.stackdump

# --- Linux ---

# Backup files created by many Linux text editors (nano, gedit)
*~
# Temporary files created by FUSE mounts
.fuse_hidden*
# KDE Dolphin folder metadata
.directory
# Per-user trash directories on Linux filesystems
.Trash-*
# Stale NFS lock files left after a crash
.nfs*


# =============================================================================
# SECTION 2 — EDITORS & IDEs
# Each editor stores its own project config, workspace state, and plugin data
# locally. These are personal preferences — forcing them on collaborators breaks
# their setup and creates pointless conflicts.
# =============================================================================

# --- Visual Studio Code ---

# Workspace settings, launch configs, extension recommendations
.vscode/
# Exception: shared formatter/linting rules are useful to commit
!.vscode/settings.json
# Exception: recommended extensions list can be shared
!.vscode/extensions.json
# Exception: shared debug launch configs
!.vscode/launch.json
# Local History extension — per-machine edit history
.history/
# VS Code extension package (binary build artifact)
*.vsix

# --- JetBrains IDEs (IntelliJ, PyCharm, WebStorm, GoLand, Rider) ---

# Entire IDE project directory (workspace, run configs, indexes)
.idea/
# Exception: shared code style settings
!.idea/codeStyles/
# Exception: shared inspection (lint) profiles
!.idea/inspectionProfiles/
# IntelliJ workspace file — machine-specific open tabs / layout
*.iws
# IntelliJ module file — auto-regenerated from build tool
*.iml
# IntelliJ project file (old format, replaced by .idea/)
*.ipr
# IntelliJ default compiled-output directory
out/
# CLion CMake build directories
cmake-build-*/

# --- Eclipse ---

# Eclipse project descriptor — contains machine-specific paths
.project
# Eclipse Java classpath — rebuilt by Maven/Gradle
.classpath
# Eclipse per-project settings (formatter, compiler)
.settings/
# Eclipse PHP project loadpath
.loadpath
# Eclipse PHP build path
.buildpath
# Eclipse default Java bytecode output folder
bin/

# --- NetBeans ---

# NetBeans private project files (machine-specific)
nbproject/private/
# NetBeans build output
nbbuild/
# NetBeans distribution output
nbdist/
# NetBeans Gradle support cache
.nb-gradle/

# --- Vim / Neovim ---

# Vim swap file — open-file recovery buffer
*.swp
# Vim secondary swap file
*.swo
# Vim tertiary swap file
*.swn
# Vim netrw browsing history
.netrwhist
# Vim session file — restores window layout / open files
Session.vim
# Local Vim config directory
.vim/
# ctags/cscope tag file — auto-generated code index
tags

# --- Emacs ---

# Emacs auto-save file (created on crash, deleted on clean exit)
